text:
SSC CGL 2016 Tier II Exam 2016 results expected today education Updated: Feb 28, 2017 16:12 IST Nilesh Mathur Hindustan Times, New Delhi The Staff Selection Commission (SSC) is likely to declare the results the Combined Graduate Level (CGL) Tier-II Examination, 2016 on its official website on Tuesday. (Ravi Kumar/HT file) 
The Staff Selection Commission (SSC) is likely to declare the results of the Combined Graduate Level (CGL) Tier-II Examination 2016 on its official website on Tuesday. 
The commission conducted the CGL Tier II exam from November 30 to December 2, 2016, and held the re-examination on January 12 and 13, 2017. It will conduct the CGL Tier-III Examination, 2016 on March 19. 
The commission issued a status report on the publication of the results earlier this month, saying they will be declared tentatively on February 28. 
Candidates can check the results here after they have been declared.. Read more
